description.plain:
David Burd, better know as “Lil Dicky”, is an American Jewish rapper who was born and raised in Cheltenham, a small suburb of Philadelphia. He first attracted attention through his viral song/video “Ex-Boyfriend,” which gained over a million views the first day it was uploaded. The song was featured on his very successful debut mixtape entitled So Hard.

His debut album Professional Rapper was released on July 31, 2015.
The album debuted as the Number One Rap Album, Number One Comedy Album, Number One Independent Album, and Number One Digital Album on the Billboard charts, and Number One overall on iTunes.

Since then, he has gone on to win the People’s Choice Webby Award for Best Online Film and Video: Music Video, and was chosen as one of XXL’s Freshman Class 2016, following in the footsteps of prior “class members” such as Kendrick Lamar, Wiz Khalifa, and many others.

songs.full_title: What To Do After a Car Accident by Lil Dicky
songs.title: What To Do After a Car Accident
songs.title_with_featured: What To Do After a Car Accident
songs.lyrics:
If you have been involved in a motor vehicle accident, it is likely that you are confused as to what your next course of action should be. This is very common in that when in a motor vehicle accident takes place, the parties thereto are initially in a state of shock. However, once that shock wears off, they begin to question what their next steps should be.

At the time of the accident, the parties to a motor vehicle accident are not in the state of mind to make any decisions or any statements. It is very common that the most important thing to the parties is their physical well-being and condition of their vehicles. Once the shock and the adrenaline has worn off, the parties are able to think clearly and that is the time to consult with and retain a Los Angeles accident attorney.

There are several reasons to retain an auto injury attorney. First is that the car accident personal injury lawyer is trained in handling the immediate next steps following a motor vehicle accident. Most often, these immediate next steps are filing a claim with the insurance carrier for the offending vehicle and filing a claim with your insurance carrier so that your medical expenses can be paid.

By and large, the parties to motor vehicle accidents are not in the frame of mind post-accident to deal with the numerous factors that are required of personal injury plaintiffs. Negotiating with insurance carriers, sending photographs, making witness statements and dealing with medical billing companies are not matters that injured parties should be concerned with. The reason for this is that an injured plaintiff has enough on their hands in terms of dealing with the recovery from the serious and possibly permanent personal injuries they sustained in the accident.

Recuperation from personal injuries can be very time-consuming depending upon their nature and extent. It is likely that an injured plaintiff will need to treat with their physician 3-4 times a week if not more. Chiropractic care, physical therapy and diagnostic testing are all routine courses of care that should be sought by personal entry plaintiffs immediately following their accident.

This leaves very little time for plaintiffs to take phone calls from insurance carriers and handle medical billing claims. Such matters are best left to a car accident personal injury lawyer since they are better prepared to handle such matters.

Therefore, the immediate two steps following a motor vehicle accident should be to consult with and retain a Los Angeles accident attorney, file a claim with the offending vehicle’s insurance carrier and file a claim with your own insurance carrier so that your medical benefits will be paid.

Beyond these main initial three steps, you should gather all of your relevant insurance documentation such as the declaration page for the policy insurance that covered your vehicle on the date of the accident. If you have photographs of your vehicle or your injuries, they should be printed and provided to your attorney on the date of your initial consultation or within at least a few days thereafter. These documents are vital to your auto injury attorney so that he or she may best advocate your case during the course of time they are negotiating with the insurance carrier for the defendant or their attorneys if your case needs to be litigated.

Your auto injury attorney will file your claim with the offending vehicle’s insurance carrier and attempt to settle your case before filing a lawsuit. However, if your case is ubable to be settled for a fair amount, your attorney will seek damages by filing a lawsuit in a Court of competent jurisdiction. This means that your case will be assigned a presiding judge and that the offending vehicle will retain counsel to defend the case.

In every motor vehicle accident case, there are two main aspects: liability and damages. Liability is where the question is asked “who is responsible?”. Depending upon the type of accident you had, liability maybe clear-cut (hit in the rear accident) or it may be disputed (left turn in front, broadside hit, T-bone accident). These are matters for your Los Angeles accident attorney to determine only after a full evaluation of your case.

As for damages, permanency is the key to the kingdom. If you have sustained permanent injuries, your case will be evaluated favorably and you will be paid for your pain and suffering. You are also entitled to compensation for lost wages and future medical treatment. Your attorney will put together a “specials” package that will make a demand upon the insurance carrier for the defendant based upon your theory of liability and the damages you sustained as a result of the accident.

It is for these reasons that you should immediately consult with and retain an experienced personal injury attorney if you have been involved in a motor vehicle accident. Your attorney will be able to recommend a skilled chiropractor and physical therapist so that you may begin to rehabilitate from your injuries. If you have a physician that you have been treating with your entire life, it is recommended that you schedule an appointment to be examined by that physician.

Take the immediate steps following your motor vehicle accident seriously since every decision you make will have far-reaching effects. If you have injuries at the time of the accident and are not feeling like yourself, do not decline medical treatment-have the ambulance take you to the emergency room so that you can be checked out. If you do not, the insurance carrier for the defendant will certainly hold this against you for as long as your case is pending. They will invariably say “if the plaintiff was that injured they would’ve gone to the emergency room”. This is a common rebuttal asserted by the defendant’s insurance carrier.

This is only one example of how crucial each decision you make is during the pendency of your case.

With that in mind, once you have settled down post-accident, contact an experienced person injury attorney and consult with them so you may take the first step toward rehabilitation, recuperation and receiving compensation for the damages you sustained in your accident.

songs.full_title: What steps should employees take if employers fail to pay overtime wages? by Lil Dicky
songs.title: What steps should employees take if employers fail to pay overtime wages?
songs.title_with_featured: What steps should employees take if employers fail to pay overtime wages?
songs.lyrics:
How does it feel when employers don’t pay their employees despite putting relentless efforts in their job duties? Working for 8 or more hours a day is hectic but it’s quite frustrating when employees don’t get pay for that. It’s a law in California that the non-exempt employees have to be given minimum wages, overtime wages, and wages of accrued vacation by their employers. If the employers fail to pay the due wages on time, they can be sued by the employees.

However, workers should consult with overtime attorneys for legal advice. In this context, it’s important to know the steps that the employees can take if their employers refuse to pay overtime wages.
First of all, employees can resign from the job without any notice and then take a legal action against the employer. If employees are wondering that how do I write my two weeks notice need to understand that in wage and hour violations, no employee is bound to give any notice! Besides this, there’s no compulsion in California to submit an advanced notice of two weeks. This is because employment in California works on an at-will basis.

California has stringent protection laws directed for employment protection. One such law is the protection of the employee from employer retaliation due to filing of a lawsuit against them.

What is the overtime wage violation?
Before proceeding with the other steps, one should know what overtime wage violation means in California. The maximum time of work is 8 hours a day or 40 hours a week in California. If an employee is made to work for more than 8 hours a day or 40 hours a week; the employer should pay for that. Failure to pay overtime wages is a violation of the California Wage and Hour Laws. Employees should seek professional help for overtime wage violation in:

•	Overtime violations
•	Misclassification of employees as independent contractors
•	Incorrect breaks
•	Denial of paying commissions
•	Miscalculation of wages

However, an exempt employee cannot make any claims or file a lawsuit because the California law doesn’t entitle them to minimum wages or overtime wages. Exempt employees are salaried persons and they are the ones involved in executive, administrative and managerial tasks. So if employees are denied overtime wages, they can file a lawsuit against the employer.

Miscalculation of wages/Commissions:
At times, employers often miscalculate wages. If a worker feels that the wages have been miscalculated should seek professional help from an attorney. They can calculate the wages and commissions and will be able to tell if it is correct to file a lawsuit. They can suggest alternative options to sort out the matter with the employers- for example, front to front discussion with the employer. However, if none of the solutions work, then filing a lawsuit would be the last resort.

Missed meal and rest breaks
Every company should offer meal and rest breaks to the employees. Under the California and federal laws, all the non-exempt employees are entitled to uninterrupted rest and meal breaks. However, if the employer makes the employee work even during the break periods, then it will be considered as a violation of the labor laws.
It’s important for the workers to seek professional help from attorneys if they’ve been denied the overtime wages.

songs.title_with_featured: What is a torque wrench and how to buy the best quality tool online?
songs.lyrics:
Different types of torque wrenches deliver different amounts of torque. There are two main types of torque wrenches used in auto repair: manual and pneumatic wrenches. Within these, there are some subcategories. For all these keys, keep in mind that it is essential to take proper care of them and calibrate them regularly to keep them working properly. No matter what type of torque wrench you ultimately choose, be sure to buy a torque wrench that meets your specific needs. To facilitate your buying, visit this website and get a perfect idea on different types of torque-wrenches available in the market. Compare the best models and know all the details.

What is a toruqe-wrench?
It is a wrench that indicates the torque that is being exercised with it. A function not only useful, but necessary: if you want to do mechanical work with precision. Most screws in a car should be tightened with the force indicated by the manufacturer. Turning more vigorously than you can can damage parts that would fail to do their job properly. The tightening torque is indicated in the manufacturer's workshop manual, although information on each model is circulated in various specialized forums.

Few basic aspects to know
Depending on the type of key, it will work in one way or another. If it is a mechanical jump key, it will simply “jump” when we reach the pair that we have selected. On the other hand, if it is a digital torque wrench, it will emit a sound or a vibration when we reach that point. There are also torque wrenches, which mark the torque using a needle.

Select the pair –Choose the necessary torque for the screw in question. On mechanical jump wrenches, it is done by turning a thread until the gauge is where you need to be. In the thread there is also a kind of ruler, which will allow you to tune more.

Slow movements –Torque wrenches should be turned slowly and steadily. This is how they work with their maximum accuracy.

For as soon as the indicator jumps –On the jump keys a clack will sound when it reaches the correct pair. On the digital keys it will beep. When that time comes you should immediately stop squeezing.
Do not use it in the opposite direction –If you use a wrench of this type to loosen instead of tightening, the most normal thing is that you end up miscalibrating . This means that it will no longer offer a correct torque measurement.

Opinions and final conclusions
There are professional torque wrenches with great precision and a very wide range of torque measurements. However, its price can be 10 or 15 times higher than the most mundane keys. If you are going to do mechanical work, it is better to get two different wrenches to cover a range of Nm wide enough. Your investment will be much less than if you bought a professional key. The torque wrench provides the necessary precision for mechanics.
